    "discriminators": [
     "A slow leak. Same stationary-noise morphology as AIR-BLOW, separated on three orthogonal axes at once. LEVEL: root_mean_square_level ~0.03 and lufs ~-34, roughly a factor of five below BLOW — a flat tire is not loud. HF TILT: high_band_energy ~0.72 (gated >= 0.20), zero_crossings_per_second ~7000, spectral_centroid_hz ~5.5 kHz — about double BLOW on every brightness feature, because a small orifice leaking slowly radiates almost nothing below 1 kHz. DURATION: tens of seconds, because the reservoir empties slowly.",
     "Not AIR-BURST: gated to at least 0.5 s with crest_factor below 12. A hiss contains no transient at all.",
     "Not AIR-SUCTION: envelope_temporal_centroid sits flat at ~0.50 and stationarity is ~0.86; SUCTION swells and is gated at envelope_temporal_centroid >= 0.40 with an expected ~0.63.",
     "The harmonicity ceiling (0.55) keeps a whistling leak from stealing WIND-TONAL's territory."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "AIRBlow",
     "AIRSuck",
     "AIRMisc",
     "AIRBrst"
    ]
   }
